{"type":"message","id":"3c7fc475","parentId":"96e0f79c","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:56:14.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hey Andre! 👋\n\nYou asked about Codex — which one are you referring to? There are a few things called \"Codex\":\n\n1. **OpenAI Codex** (the AI code model) — deprecated by OpenAI, replaced by GPT-4 and Codex CLI\n2. **OpenAI Codex CLI** — a terminal-based AI coding agent, currently **free** while in research preview (you need an API key, which has usage-based pricing, but the CLI tool itself is gratis)\n3. **Codex by another provider** — any number of niche tools\n\nDid you mean the OpenAI Codex CLI? That's been making waves lately as a terminal-native coding agent."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":10976,"output":152,"cacheRead":6528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17656,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779774960220,"responseId":"gen-1779774960-GXuKeQQZUCoaPMFqee3f"}}
