{"type":"message","id":"fe958e7f","parentId":"9c3da915","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:57:56.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's what I know:\n\n**OpenAI Codex CLI** (the terminal coding agent launched in April 2025):\n\n- The **CLI tool itself is free** to install and use\n- It calls the OpenAI API under the hood, so you pay for API usage\n- For free-tier OpenAI API users: it works with the **free tier models** (like `gpt-4o-mini`), which gives you a limited number of tokens per month at no cost\n- For ChatGPT Pro subscribers ($200/mo): you get included usage\n\nSo the short answer: **yes, it's free to install**, and you can use it with free-tier API credits for light usage. For heavier work, you'd need API credits or a Pro subscription.\n\nWant me to help you get it set up?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1184,"output":172,"cacheRead":17792,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779775067022,"responseId":"gen-1779775067-sbDXMkCguA0q02FqBlCl"}}
