{"type":"message","id":"54d9ff49","parentId":"bbc0fd58","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:59:00.706Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So Codex CLI isn't installed yet. Here's the deal:\n\n**Codex CLI ≠ FreeRide** — they serve different purposes:\n\n- **FreeRide** = configures OpenClaw to use free OpenRouter models for *my* responses (that's what you have running right now — I'm on `openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha`)\n- **Codex CLI** = a separate terminal tool from OpenAI that writes/runs code for you interactively. It's an agent that lives in your shell, not inside OpenClaw\n\n**Can Codex CLI work with free models?** It primarily uses OpenAI's API. But there's a workaround — you can point it at OpenRouter as a custom provider, which would let it use the **same free models** FreeRide sets up. So in theory:\n\n1. FreeRide configures free OpenRouter models\n2. Codex CLI connects to OpenRouter API\n3. You get Codex's coding agent for free (within OpenRouter's free model limits)\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Install Codex CLI** and try wiring it up to OpenRouter for free usage?\n2. Or just stick with the current FreeRide setup and use me for coding tasks through OpenClaw?\n\nWhat's the goal — do you want a terminal-native coding agent, or are you looking to improve the code I generate here?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1370,"output":293,"cacheRead":19328,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20991,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779775129167,"responseId":"gen-1779775129-rp0va9zBinUvIaccLwJx"}}
{"type":"message","id":"41b8ec07-c35b-4f71-9ee3-b39ae7b34cc3","parentId":"54d9ff49","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:59:02.147Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So Codex CLI isn't installed yet. Here's the deal:\n\n**Codex CLI ≠ FreeRide** — they serve different purposes:\n\n- **FreeRide** = configures OpenClaw to use free OpenRouter models for *my* responses (that's what you have running right now — I'm on `openrouter/openrouter/owl-alpha`)\n- **Codex CLI** = a separate terminal tool from OpenAI that writes/runs code for you interactively. It's an agent that lives in your shell, not inside OpenClaw\n\n**Can Codex CLI work with free models?** It primarily uses OpenAI's API. But there's a workaround — you can point it at OpenRouter as a custom provider, which would let it use the **same free models** FreeRide sets up. So in theory:\n\n1. FreeRide configures free OpenRouter models\n2. Codex CLI connects to OpenRouter API\n3. You get Codex's coding agent for free (within OpenRouter's free model limits)\n\nWant me to:\n1. **Install Codex CLI** and try wiring it up to OpenRouter for free usage?\n2. Or just stick with the current FreeRide setup and use me for coding tasks through OpenClaw?\n\nWhat's the goal — do you want a terminal-native coding agent, or are you looking to improve the code I generate here?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779775142144}}
