{"type":"message","id":"f735020d","parentId":"d5de85d1","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:04:56.831Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK, the `--oss` flag is for local providers (Ollama/LMStudio). For OpenRouter, the approach is to use the API key method. Let me try the simplest approach — set the `OPENAI_API_KEY` to the OpenRouter key and use a custom base URL via config:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"c3f4dacd-ae71-4708-8bd2-a6060a6eaa91","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.codex/config.toml","content":"model = \"qwen/qwen3-coder:free\"\n\n[model_providers.openrouter]\nname = \"OpenRouter\"\nbase_url = \"https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\"\nenv_key = \"OPENROUTER_API_KEY\"\nwire_api = \"responses\"\nmodels = [\n  { id = \"qwen/qwen3-coder:free\", name = \"Qwen3 Coder (free)\" },\n  { id = \"qwen/qwen3-coder\", name = \"Qwen3 Coder\" },\n]\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"~/.codex/config.toml\", \"content\": \"model = \\\"qwen/qwen3-coder:free\\\"\\n\\n[model_providers.openrouter]\\nname = \\\"OpenRouter\\\"\\nbase_url = \\\"https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\\\"\\nenv_key = \\\"OPENROUTER_API_KEY\\\"\\nwire_api = \\\"responses\\\"\\nmodels = [\\n  { id = \\\"qwen/qwen3-coder:free\\\", name = \\\"Qwen3 Coder (free)\\\" },\\n  { id = \\\"qwen/qwen3-coder\\\", name = \\\"Qwen3 Coder\\\" },\\n]\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":183,"output":198,"cacheRead":31232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31613,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779775483603,"responseId":"gen-1779775483-SS4N4xyQKVFiHFYXuM29"}}
