{"type":"message","id":"22808e7a","parentId":"1b56117b","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:06:02.046Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"015ea391-1bef-4812-bc4a-6752bb0de000","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage login\n\nUsage: codex login [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]\n\nCommands:\n  status  Show login status\n  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\n\nOptions:\n  -c, --config <key=value>\n          Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`.\n          Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed\n          as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.\n          \n          Examples: - `-c model=\"o3\"` - `-c 'sandbox_permissions=[\"disk-full-read-access\"]'` - `-c\n          shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`\n\n      --with-api-key\n          Read the API key from stdin (e.g. `printenv OPENAI_API_KEY | codex login --with-api-key`)\n\n      --enable <FEATURE>\n          Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `-c features.<name>=true`\n\n      --with-access-token\n          Read the access token from stdin (e.g. `printenv CODEX_ACCESS_TOKEN | codex login\n          --with-access-token`)\n\n      --disable <FEATURE>\n          Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `-c features.<name>=false`\n\n      --device-auth\n          \n\n  -h, --help\n          Print help (see a summary with '-h')"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":68,"aggregated":"Manage login\n\nUsage: codex login [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]\n\nCommands:\n  status  Show login status\n  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\n\nOptions:\n  -c, --config <key=value>\n          Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`.\n          Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed\n          as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.\n          \n          Examples: - `-c model=\"o3\"` - `-c 'sandbox_permissions=[\"disk-full-read-access\"]'` - `-c\n          shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`\n\n      --with-api-key\n          Read the API key from stdin (e.g. `printenv OPENAI_API_KEY | codex login --with-api-key`)\n\n      --enable <FEATURE>\n          Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `-c features.<name>=true`\n\n      --with-access-token\n          Read the access token from stdin (e.g. `printenv CODEX_ACCESS_TOKEN | codex login\n          --with-access-token`)\n\n      --disable <FEATURE>\n          Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `-c features.<name>=false`\n\n      --device-auth\n          \n\n  -h, --help\n          Print help (see a summary with '-h')","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779775562046}}
{"type":"message","id":"5256abc1","parentId":"22808e7a","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:06:18.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`--with-api-key` — that's what I need. But that expects an OpenAI API key. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe core issue: **Codex CLI is designed for OpenAI's Responses API**, which is proprietary. OpenRouter doesn't proxy the Responses API (only Chat Completions). So Codex CLI can't directly use OpenRouter as a provider through its normal config.\n\nThe options are:\n\n1. **Use Codex CLI with an OpenAI API key** — pay OpenAI directly for usage\n2. **Use it with ChatGPT subscription** — included in ChatGPT Plus/Pro\n3. **Use OpenRouter's Chat Completions via a different tool** (not Codex)\n\nLet me reset the config and give you the honest picture:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"41d8b9e0-71ff-48e7-aa57-85541b6442d1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"rm ~/.codex/config.toml"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"rm ~/.codex/config.toml\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":429,"output":183,"cacheRead":32000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32612,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779775562047,"responseId":"gen-1779775562-J6JQVwa48zrhJaT7w3jt"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3c7e5fa","parentId":"5256abc1","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:06:18.762Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"41d8b9e0-71ff-48e7-aa57-85541b6442d1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"(no output)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8,"aggregated":"","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779775578761}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8ac089a","parentId":"e3c7e5fa","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:06:40.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the situation:\n\n**Codex CLI unfortunately doesn't support OpenRouter out of the box.** It uses OpenAI's proprietary Responses API, and OpenRouter only proxies the standard Chat Completions API. So our FreeRide/OpenRouter setup can't be used with Codex.\n\nYour options:\n\n1. **Get an OpenAI API key** — put $5-10 of credits on it, wire that to Codex. Cheap, you only pay per use.\n2. **ChatGPT Pro subscription** ($200/mo) — includes Codex usage, no per-token billing. Overkill if you just want a coding agent.\n3. **Keep using me (OpenClaw) through FreeRide** — I can already spawn sub-agents, run code, edit files, and review code, all on free OpenRouter models. For many coding workflows, this is enough.\n\nI'd recommend **option 1** if you really want Codex. A few bucks in OpenAI API credits goes a long way. Want me to help set that up?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":246,"output":224,"cacheRead":32384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32854,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779775578763,"responseId":"gen-1779775578-KeposDPhNwAyA3Wo4inf"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ecae306-1e1c-4415-a8c0-1d172eba5c8c","parentId":"e8ac089a","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:06:41.850Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the situation:\n\n**Codex CLI unfortunately doesn't support OpenRouter out of the box.** It uses OpenAI's proprietary Responses API, and OpenRouter only proxies the standard Chat Completions API. So our FreeRide/OpenRouter setup can't be used with Codex.\n\nYour options:\n\n1. **Get an OpenAI API key** — put $5-10 of credits on it, wire that to Codex. Cheap, you only pay per use.\n2. **ChatGPT Pro subscription** ($200/mo) — includes Codex usage, no per-token billing. Overkill if you just want a coding agent.\n3. **Keep using me (OpenClaw) through FreeRide** — I can already spawn sub-agents, run code, edit files, and review code, all on free OpenRouter models. For many coding workflows, this is enough.\n\nI'd recommend **option 1** if you really want Codex. A few bucks in OpenAI API credits goes a long way. Want me to help set that up?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779775601847}}
{"type":"message","id":"545b235e","parentId":"0ecae306-1e1c-4415-a8c0-1d172eba5c8c","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:06:42.124Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"1835\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-05-26 07:03 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#1812 Tue 2026-05-26 06:11 GMT+1 Andre: Is codex free to use\n#1814 Tue 2026-05-26 06:15 GMT+1 Andre: Hm\n#1816 Tue 2026-05-26 06:50 GMT+1 Andre: Hi\n#1818 Tue 2026-05-26 06:55 GMT+1 Andre: Hi\n#1820 Tue 2026-05-26 06:57 GMT+1 Andre: Yes CLI, to improve coding output\n#1824 Tue 2026-05-26 06:58 GMT+1 Andre: How does this work with our setup I.e free ride\n#1826 Tue 2026-05-26 07:00 GMT+1 Andre: Both, yes setup\n\nIf it doesn’t exist and allow for custom providers"}],"timestamp":1779775602118}}
