{"type":"message","id":"7428bdee","parentId":"72e6a1e1","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:06:54.152Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"17110021-a45f-4052-8a20-11640d64ac8d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"doctor          Diagnose local Codex installation, config, auth, and runtime health\n  apply           Apply the latest diff produced by Codex agent as a `git apply` to your local\n  cloud           [EXPERIMENTAL] Browse tasks from Codex Cloud and apply changes locally\n          Use open-source provider\n      --local-provider <OSS_PROVIDER>\n          Specify which local provider to use (lmstudio or ollama). If not specified with --oss,\n          Layer $CODEX_HOME/<name>.config.toml on top of the base user config"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":75,"aggregated":"doctor          Diagnose local Codex installation, config, auth, and runtime health\n  apply           Apply the latest diff produced by Codex agent as a `git apply` to your local\n  cloud           [EXPERIMENTAL] Browse tasks from Codex Cloud and apply changes locally\n          Use open-source provider\n      --local-provider <OSS_PROVIDER>\n          Specify which local provider to use (lmstudio or ollama). If not specified with --oss,\n          Layer $CODEX_HOME/<name>.config.toml on top of the base user config","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779775614151}}
{"type":"message","id":"768b5e01","parentId":"7428bdee","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:07:10.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So the only provider options are:\n- **OpenAI** (default, Responses API)\n- **Local OSS** (Ollama or LMStudio via `--oss`)\n\nThere's **no custom provider / base URL support** in v0.133.0. Codex is locked to OpenAI's ecosystem.\n\nHere's what you *can* do though:\n\n1. **Use Codex with Ollama locally** — `codex --oss --local-provider ollama`. Run a free local model like `qwen2.5-coder`. This is completely free, no API keys needed, runs on your Mac's GPU. The catch: requires Ollama installed and a local model downloaded.\n\n2. **Use Codex with an OpenAI API key** — pay-as-you-go, a few dollars lasts a while.\n\n3. **I do it through OpenClaw** — I can already tackle coding tasks using free OpenRouter models via sub-agents. Not as polished as a dedicated terminal agent, but it works.\n\nWant me to set up the **Ollama route**? That would give you a free Codex-like terminal coding agent running locally on your Mac, no subscription or API key needed."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":328,"output":253,"cacheRead":33024,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33605,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779775614153,"responseId":"gen-1779775614-A6NQXjCcYYV2Vii0NuS4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bae35d6e-04df-4301-b87c-5f991fb1fce3","parentId":"768b5e01","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:07:12.508Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"So the only provider options are:\n- **OpenAI** (default, Responses API)\n- **Local OSS** (Ollama or LMStudio via `--oss`)\n\nThere's **no custom provider / base URL support** in v0.133.0. Codex is locked to OpenAI's ecosystem.\n\nHere's what you *can* do though:\n\n1. **Use Codex with Ollama locally** — `codex --oss --local-provider ollama`. Run a free local model like `qwen2.5-coder`. This is completely free, no API keys needed, runs on your Mac's GPU. The catch: requires Ollama installed and a local model downloaded.\n\n2. **Use Codex with an OpenAI API key** — pay-as-you-go, a few dollars lasts a while.\n\n3. **I do it through OpenClaw** — I can already tackle coding tasks using free OpenRouter models via sub-agents. Not as polished as a dedicated terminal agent, but it works.\n\nWant me to set up the **Ollama route**? That would give you a free Codex-like terminal coding agent running locally on your Mac, no subscription or API key needed."}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779775632506}}
{"type":"message","id":"72188d28","parentId":"bae35d6e-04df-4301-b87c-5f991fb1fce3","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:07:13.182Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"1836\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-05-26 07:03 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#1812 Tue 2026-05-26 06:11 GMT+1 Andre: Is codex free to use\n#1814 Tue 2026-05-26 06:15 GMT+1 Andre: Hm\n#1816 Tue 2026-05-26 06:50 GMT+1 Andre: Hi\n#1818 Tue 2026-05-26 06:55 GMT+1 Andre: Hi\n#1820 Tue 2026-05-26 06:57 GMT+1 Andre: Yes CLI, to improve coding output\n#1824 Tue 2026-05-26 06:58 GMT+1 Andre: How does this work with our setup I.e free ride\n#1826 Tue 2026-05-26 07:00 GMT+1 Andre: Both, yes setup\n#1835 Tue 2026-05-26 07:03 GMT+1 Andre: If it doesn’t exist and allow for custom providers\n\nNo need to build from scratch, what does the docs state, do you need me to find that info 2 secs"}],"timestamp":1779775633176}}
