{"type":"message","id":"8fa670c6","parentId":"b7dda5a0","timestamp":"2026-05-26T06:12:06.396Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nAlright, stopping the deep dive. Let me clean up and give you practical answers.\n\n**On Codex + OpenRouter:** Codex CLI is hardcoded to `api.openai.com` (OpenAI's proprietary Responses API). It can't use OpenRouter or any custom provider — confirmed from reading the Rust source. So this path is dead unless you get an OpenAI API key or ChatGPT subscription.\n\n**On your questions about free coding agents with FreeRide:** There are a few that work with OpenRouter:\n\n1. **aider** — popular terminal coding agent, supports OpenRouter via `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` env var and `--model` flag\n2. **goose** — from block/mcp, supports OpenRouter\n3. **CLI-Anything / OpenCode** — terminal agents with OpenRouter support\n\nLet me check what's available and install one:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"9eded466-caab-4a62-a7d6-42bd832724f3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which aider 2>/dev/null; which goose 2>/dev/null; which opencode 2>/dev/null; npm list -g 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"aider\\|goose\\|opencode\\|codex\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"which aider 2>/dev/null; which goose 2>/dev/null; which opencode 2>/dev/null; npm list -g 2>/dev/null | grep -i \\\"aider\\\\|goose\\\\|opencode\\\\|codex\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":11876,"output":248,"cacheRead":53248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65372,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779775896378,"responseId":"gen-1779775896-ujtPIsWwb10i1LRBiwX4"}}
