{"type":"message","id":"1088a4a0","parentId":"09907480","timestamp":"2026-05-26T08:26:52.209Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the summary:\n\n**Codex CLI** — confirmed it's locked to OpenAI's Responses API (`api.openai.com`). No custom provider support, no OpenRouter compatibility. Uninstalled.\n\n**aider** — works great with OpenRouter, was installed and verified, but you asked to uninstall. Easy to reinstall anytime.\n\n**OpenCode** — open source, nice terminal UI, supports any provider including OpenRouter. Also uninstalled.\n\n**Bottom line:** Your current setup (OpenClaw + FreeRide + free OpenRouter models) already handles coding tasks well through sub-agents. If you want a dedicated terminal coding agent later, `aider` is the quickest path — just `pip3 install aider-chat` and point it at `openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free`.\n\nAnything else you want to tackle?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":54802,"output":178,"cacheRead":5376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60356,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779783995230,"responseId":"gen-1779783995-W4GcjueJKsm9No6oBjIy"}}
