{"type":"message","id":"8f8199bd","parentId":"cf2e4610-b1a5-4d0c-9bfd-ac284bcbe67b","timestamp":"2026-05-26T19:20:55.178Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"1861\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-05-26 20:20 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#1835 Tue 2026-05-26 07:03 GMT+1 Andre: If it doesn’t exist and allow for custom providers\n#1836 Tue 2026-05-26 07:03 GMT+1 Andre: No need to build from scratch, what does the docs state, do you need me to find that info 2 secs\n#1841 Tue 2026-05-26 07:04 GMT+1 Andre: https://context7.com/openai/codex/llms.txt?tokens=10000\n#1848 Tue 2026-05-26 07:08 GMT+1 Andre: If it was setup in the Mac terminal way, will the free version work well for a while or does it get used up quickly\n#1849 Tue 2026-05-26 07:08 GMT+1 Andre: Is there any free coding agents that can use freeride\n#1850 Tue 2026-05-26 07:08 GMT+1 Andre: To enhance coding capabilities\n#1853 Tue 2026-05-26 07:10 GMT+1 Andre: Stop the codex schema\n#1856 Tue 2026-05-26 07:15 GMT+1 Andre: Yes uninstall\n#1857 Tue 2026-05-26 09:26 GMT+1 Andre: How did it go\n#1859 Tue 2026-05-26 19:46 GMT+1 Andre: What’s aider\n\nWould aider benefit our setup"}],"timestamp":1779823255172}}
{"type":"message","id":"57c8c648","parentId":"8f8199bd","timestamp":"2026-05-26T19:21:09.619Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes, actually. Here's why:\n\n**aider + FreeRide would be a good fit:**\n\n- **Free** — runs on our OpenRouter free models (`qwen3-coder:free`)\n- **Terminal-native** — lives in your shell, not in OpenClaw's session\n- **Multi-file aware** — understands your whole codebase, makes coordinated edits across files\n- **Git-integrated** — auto-commits with diffs, easy to review changes\n- **Fast iteration** — lightweight compared to spinning up sub-agents for every coding task\n\n**Use case:** When you're working on Mission Control (or any project) in your terminal and want an AI pair programmer that can edit multiple files, understand git history, and iterate quickly — aider is purpose-built for that.\n\nThrough OpenClaw, I can already do code generation and file edits, but aider would give you a **dedicated terminal experience** that's faster for back-and-forth coding sessions.\n\nWant me to reinstall it and set it up with FreeRide?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":51328,"output":222,"cacheRead":9984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61534,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779823255184,"responseId":"gen-1779823255-l1j4Wx2VEOT83KJDndKX"}}
{"type":"message","id":"240e8ef4-12ed-41e2-91fa-a0fa70771388","parentId":"57c8c648","timestamp":"2026-05-26T19:21:11.169Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes, actually. Here's why:\n\n**aider + FreeRide would be a good fit:**\n\n- **Free** — runs on our OpenRouter free models (`qwen3-coder:free`)\n- **Terminal-native** — lives in your shell, not in OpenClaw's session\n- **Multi-file aware** — understands your whole codebase, makes coordinated edits across files\n- **Git-integrated** — auto-commits with diffs, easy to review changes\n- **Fast iteration** — lightweight compared to spinning up sub-agents for every coding task\n\n**Use case:** When you're working on Mission Control (or any project) in your terminal and want an AI pair programmer that can edit multiple files, understand git history, and iterate quickly — aider is purpose-built for that.\n\nThrough OpenClaw, I can already do code generation and file edits, but aider would give you a **dedicated terminal experience** that's faster for back-and-forth coding sessions.\n\nWant me to reinstall it and set it up with FreeRide?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779823271167}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a8ede64","parentId":"240e8ef4-12ed-41e2-91fa-a0fa70771388","timestamp":"2026-05-26T19:24:12.189Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n  \"message_id\": \"1863\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"sender\": \"Andre\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-05-26 20:24 GMT+1\",\n  \"inbound_event_kind\": \"user_request\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Andre (7507878944)\",\n  \"id\": \"7507878944\",\n  \"name\": \"Andre\",\n  \"username\": \"mayhomme\"\n}\n```\n\nConversation context (untrusted, chronological, selected for current message):\n#1836 Tue 2026-05-26 07:03 GMT+1 Andre: No need to build from scratch, what does the docs state, do you need me to find that info 2 secs\n#1841 Tue 2026-05-26 07:04 GMT+1 Andre: https://context7.com/openai/codex/llms.txt?tokens=10000\n#1848 Tue 2026-05-26 07:08 GMT+1 Andre: If it was setup in the Mac terminal way, will the free version work well for a while or does it get used up quickly\n#1849 Tue 2026-05-26 07:08 GMT+1 Andre: Is there any free coding agents that can use freeride\n#1850 Tue 2026-05-26 07:08 GMT+1 Andre: To enhance coding capabilities\n#1853 Tue 2026-05-26 07:10 GMT+1 Andre: Stop the codex schema\n#1856 Tue 2026-05-26 07:15 GMT+1 Andre: Yes uninstall\n#1857 Tue 2026-05-26 09:26 GMT+1 Andre: How did it go\n#1859 Tue 2026-05-26 19:46 GMT+1 Andre: What’s aider\n#1861 Tue 2026-05-26 20:20 GMT+1 Andre: Would aider benefit our setup\n\nWould you use it together i.e you can see the coding output or the output can be shared in openclaw?"}],"timestamp":1779823452183}}
{"type":"message","id":"87d45d66","parentId":"4a8ede64","timestamp":"2026-05-26T19:24:25.853Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question. There are two ways this could work:\n\n**1. Independent (terminal only)**\nYou run aider in your terminal, it edits files and commits. I can't see the live session, but I can read the resulting files, diffs, and git history afterward. This is fine but siloed.\n\n**2. Integrated through OpenClaw**\nThis is where it gets interesting. I could:\n- Spawn aider as a background process from within OpenClaw using `exec`\n- Feed it tasks and read its output in real-time\n- Parse the results and report back to you in Telegram\n- Even have aider do the heavy coding lifting while I handle planning, review, and coordination\n\n**Practical example:**\nInstead of me spawning sub-agents for coding tasks (which works but has overhead), I could say:\n\n> \"aider, refactor the mission-control dashboard routes to use the new API pattern\"\n\n...run it in the background, wait for the diff, review it, and show you the results. Best of both worlds — aider's coding proficiency + my orchestration.\n\n**The catch:** Runs on FreeRide's free models, so subject to rate limits on heavy sessions. But for targeted coding tasks, it should be plenty fast.\n\nWant me to install it and test this integrated approach?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1299,"output":267,"cacheRead":60672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62238,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779823452196,"responseId":"gen-1779823452-jG6rv6DGMvsKzlHpb6Y8"}}
